Subject: rPSA-2007-0241-1 samba samba-swat

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0241-1
Published: 2007-11-16
Products:
    rPath Linux 1

Rating: Critical
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote Root Deterministic Unauthorized Access
Updated Versions:
    samba=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/3.0.27-0.1-1
    samba-swat=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/3.0.27-0.1-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1894

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-4572
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-5398

Description:
    Previous versions of the samba package are vulnerable to a remote
    Arbitrary Code Execution attack when nmbd is configured as a WINS
    server.

